Newport Corp.

                    Newport Corp. manufactures and trades products and solutions for scientific research, microelectronics, security, life and health sciences, and industrial markets. It operates through the following segments: Photonics, Lasers, and Optics. The Photonics segment produces photonics instruments, precision positioning systems, vibration isolation systems, and optical components. The Lasers segment provides laser-based systems such as ultrafast lasers, amplifiers, diode-pumped solid state, tunable, and fiber lasers. The Optics segment offers lens assemblies, optical components, and opto-mechanical subassemblies. The company was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Irvine, CA.                  




Director

                    Current                  


Vamosa Ltd.

                    In today's business world, enterprise and public sector organizations are becoming increasingly 'content savvy.' Rapidly increasing volumes of content are presenting companies with many challenges from increased costs and carbon emissions to corporate inefficiencies. In addition, companies are finding that published content does not always meet corporate standards and is not compliant. The challenge faced by content owners is how to ensure that they comply with internal policy or external regulatory standards, reduce costs and carbon emissions and improve corporate efficiency all while maintaining content quality to support the business.Vamosa's solutions for Enterprise Content Governance (ECoG) allow the world's largest enterprises and governments to analyze, enhance, standardize, monitor and maintain all forms of business content within a policy-based infrastructure of best practice methods. Organizations with Vamosa's ECoG solutions benefit from improved regulatory compliance, enhanced knowledge management and a lower Total Cost of Ownership (TCO) for content management.                  




